{"tid":1659201,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[制裁港共] 英女皇演說冇講，但英國外相：脫歐後推馬格尼茨法案","createTime":"2019-10-16T23:37:55.000Z","updateTime":"2019-10-18T09:18:48.000Z","uid":311867,"like":37,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":19,"replies":[{"pid":"59577ea417c1b74195888443e1e2d37ba7fe3091","tid":1659201,"uid":311867,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-16T23:37:55.000Z","msg":"路透社 - 英國將在脫歐後推動法案，凍結資產以制裁侵害人權者。<br />\n<br />\n(Reuters) - <strong><span style=\"color: red;\">Britain will introduce laws after it leaves the European Union to freeze assets of those deemed responsible for human rights abuses, foreign minister Dominic Raab said on Sunday.</span></strong><br />\n<br />\nThe United States passed a law known as the Magnitsky Act in 2012 under which it has imposed visa bans and asset freezes on Russian officials linked to the death of Sergei Magnitsky, a Russian lawyer arrested in 2008 after alleging that Russian officials were involved in large-scale tax fraud.<br />\n<br />\nMagnitsky died in a Moscow prison in 2009 after complaining of mistreatment.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;<span style=\"color: red;\"><strong>We will bring into force a UK Magnitsky law, to place visa bans and asset freezes on those individuals deemed responsible for serious human rights abuses, including torture</strong></span>,&rdquo; Raab told the party's annual conference in Manchester.<br />\n<br />\nIn 2018, the British parliament passed a so-called 'Magnitsky amendment' to the Sanctions and Anti-Money Laundering Act to give the government the power to impose sanctions on people who commit gross human rights violations.<br />\n<br />\nRaab did not give any further details of the government's plans would differ from these existing powers.<br />\n<br />\n(Reporting by William James and Kylie MacLellan, editing by Elizabeth Piper)<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu-raab-idUSKBN1WE0IT\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-britain-eu-raab-idUSKBN1WE0IT&d=o%2BN67aGUGKsADGfJqajrgAbFtlMfP7wF5OAPhGI7yCY%3D&h=887f3b71\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-britain-eu-raab-idUSKBN1WE0IT&h=681fbd30\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu-raab-idUSKBN1WE0IT</a>"},{"pid":"7aea97004bce4a157a84d1dac9fcecc3ac1925ab","tid":1659201,"uid":63206,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-16T23:39:17.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"b6511f5e7c4b666a0549f4aebb54bc3c72e91601","tid":1659201,"uid":33579,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-16T23:41:51.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"da62f6e4a554b288a6eae39d0f3f24dd85a70623","tid":1659201,"uid":296108,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-16T23:44:32.000Z","msg":"期待中"},{"pid":"6326e1b54c919b6664ded5053488c279d02b4884","tid":1659201,"uid":219183,"like":8,"dislike":2,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-16T23:48:39.000Z","msg":"脫歐後⋯<br />\n此pi 已完"},{"pid":"a99571b311691c67ad803974d9cfabad11b1d8dd","tid":1659201,"uid":286792,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-16T23:49:20.000Z","msg":"推"},{"pid":"daef52491278e59b8a4694eed91e2f3b901136e7","tid":1659201,"uid":303862,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-16T23:55:47.000Z","msg":"英國佬係威返次先好<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/upset.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"27aac7d0b1e79a8dffbbba00da6168895a2a6a5c","tid":1659201,"uid":60563,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-17T00:26:48.000Z","msg":"可唔可以唔要脫歐後3隻字<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/sick.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"97d87b6376929ac66bdb3ec797920b377367f175","tid":1659201,"uid":10757,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-17T00:27:42.000Z","msg":"藍乜乜條友唔多信得過"},{"pid":"c9431175d3385c650305af49543261f0f11257a3","tid":1659201,"uid":15227,"li